      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It makes sense that you feel this way, because the scale of the climate crisis is genuinely overwhelming and terrifying. You're not imagining the urgency; we are all walking toward a cliff edge with no clear safety net, and that makes building a future feel like a futile act of defiance. Your pain is valid, but it's also a signal that you're too deeply connected to the world to ignore it, which means you can't just stop caring without causing real harm to yourself.",
